### =====================================================================
### HexaStock — Watchlist / Market Sentinel demo — CONTROL & CLEANUP
###
### Operational and destructive requests, kept separate from the setup
### flow so you can show activation/deactivation, alert removal, and
### watchlist deletion individually during the live demo.
###
### IMPORTANT: run ./watchlist-market-sentinel-setup.http first.
### That file initialises the global variables {{watchlistId}},
### {{portfolioId}}, {{ticker}} and {{threshold}} via
### client.global.set(...). This file reuses them with no copy-paste.
###
### Companion files:
###   - Setup script .................... ./watchlist-market-sentinel-setup.http
###   - Narrative + verification guide .. ../monday-session/DEMO-WATCHLIST-NOTIFICATION-FLOW.md
### =====================================================================

### Local default for baseUrl. {{watchlistId}}, {{portfolioId}},
### {{ticker}} and {{threshold}} are pulled from the global environment
### populated by the setup script — if they appear unresolved in the
### request preview, run the setup script first.
@baseUrl = http://localhost:8081


### -------------------------------------------------------------------
### 1) Deactivate the watchlist.
### Kill-switch: from this moment on the scheduler stops finding the
### alert (predicate fails on w.active=true) and WATCHLIST_ALERT log
### lines stop appearing. Useful to show that activation has immediate
### effect.
### -------------------------------------------------------------------
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/watchlists/{{watchlistId}}/deactivation

> {%
    client.log("watchlist " + client.global.get("watchlistId") + " is now INACTIVE");
%}


### -------------------------------------------------------------------
### 2) Re-activate the watchlist (lets the demo loop).
### -------------------------------------------------------------------
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/watchlists/{{watchlistId}}/activation

> {%
    client.log("watchlist " + client.global.get("watchlistId") + " is ACTIVE again");
%}


### -------------------------------------------------------------------
### 3) Remove ONE alert by (ticker, thresholdPrice).
### Precise removal endpoint — leaves any other alerts on the same
### ticker untouched.
### -------------------------------------------------------------------
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/watchlists/{{watchlistId}}/alerts?ticker={{ticker}}&thresholdPrice={{threshold}}


### -------------------------------------------------------------------
### 4) Remove ALL alerts for a given ticker.
### Bulk variant — wipes every threshold registered for {{ticker}}.
### Re-add the alert with the setup script's request 3 if you want to
### keep demoing.
### -------------------------------------------------------------------
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/watchlists/{{watchlistId}}/alerts/{{ticker}}


### -------------------------------------------------------------------
### 5) Delete the watchlist (final cleanup).
### After this the scheduler has nothing to poll for ownerName=alice.
### -------------------------------------------------------------------
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/watchlists/{{watchlistId}}

> {%
    client.log("watchlist " + client.global.get("watchlistId") + " deleted");
%}


### -------------------------------------------------------------------
### 6) Inspect the demo portfolio (optional — read-only).
### The portfolio API does not expose a DELETE endpoint by design;
### portfolio data is meant to be retained for audit. Use this GET to
### confirm the portfolio created by the setup script is still there.
### To wipe portfolio data between demo runs, drop the MySQL volume
### with `docker compose down -v && docker compose up -d mysql`.
### -------------------------------------------------------------------
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/portfolios/{{portfolioId}}

> {%
    if (response.status === 200) {
        client.log("portfolio " + client.global.get("portfolioId") + " owner=" + response.body.ownerName);
    } else {
        client.log("portfolio GET returned " + response.status);
    }
%}
